<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="276" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">811.113/255</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Swedish Minister</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Boström</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                            Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Castle</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-28">February 28,
                            1933</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Castle</hi>: Referring to our conversation
                        on February 9th about the Swedish Government’s willingness to cooperate with
                        the United States Government with a view to a concerted action between the
                        arms-producing countries in a certain situation, I beg to <pb facs="0465" n="363" xml:id="pg_363"/> inform you that I have now received a telegram
                        from my Government to the effect that my assumption was correct that it
                        would be willing to cooperate with your and other interested Governments in
                        the direction outlined in the resolution now before Congress.</p>
                    <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>W. <hi rend="smallcaps">Boström</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>